The 16th anniversary of The Hindu Young WorldQuiz , one of the longest-running and largest live school quizzes, will be organised in Vijayawada on Wednesday (January 20). The quiz will be hosted by The Hindu â€™s resident quizmaster V.V. Ramanan.Vijayawada Police Commissioner Gautham Sawang, the chief guest at the programme, will give away prizes to the winners.The contest will have two categories: Juniors (Classes IV to VI) and Seniors (Classes VII to IX). Junior quiz competitions will be held in Bengaluru, Hyderabad, Vijayawada and Visakhapatnam, while competitions for seniors will be held in Bengaluru, Mangaluru, Hubballi, Hyderabad, Vijayawada and Visakhapatnam.Spot registrationThe competition in Vijayawada will be conducted on January 20 at Siddhartha Academy Auditorium.Spot registrations will be held for students in the junior category from 9 a.m. onwards. The quiz programme will begin at 10 a.m.Similarly, the spot registrations for the students in the senior category will begin at 1 p.m., and the quiz will begin at 2 p.m.For those who want to register online, the last date has been extended by a day and they can register on Tuesday also. The 16th edition of the quiz is being presented (sponsored) by the Vellore Institute of Technology (VIT) and powered by the State Bank of India (SBI). Firefox is the national gift partner and Kokuyo Camlin is the goodie partner.Ilapuram Travels, Mithra Honda, Kottakkal Arya Vaidya Sala, Modern Super Market, Saahiti Prachuranalu, Sweet Magic, Ashok Book Centre and Efftronics have come forward to be the regional sponsor.Madhurams Sweets, Bakery and Coffee Shop have come forward to be the snack sponsor and Siddhartha Academy has come forward to be venue and hospitality sponsors.For further details, interested candidates can contact Vijayawada edition head V.V. Raja Rao by dialling 9849211799 or log on to www.thehindu.com/vwquiz.Those who were not able to register online can register on the spot at the venue an hour before the contest.